STOWE is Harriet Beecher Stowe, author of "Uncle Tom's Cabin", a very strong condemnation of slavery. It is credited (historians differ) with having tipped Northern sympathies more strongly into the abolitionist camp.
President Lincoln reportedly called her something like "the lady who wrote the little book that started the big war" (I may have LITTLE in the wrong position).

